"{\"uid\": \"deadline.com-2024-08-inside-look-tom-cruise-olympic-leap-la28-1236038304\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByPeter White  Executive Editor, Television  Tom Cruisehas leapt from great heights under the guidance ofBen Winston, co-founder ofFulwell73and creative producer of the Los AngelesOlympics2028 handover, one time before.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\", \"score\": 0.9999976861294666, \"rank\": 2.313792350659804e-06, \"text\": \"White\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time, however, it was different.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The whole world was watching.\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise, who previously jumped out a plane alongside James Corden onThe Late Late Show, which was exec produced by Winston, revved up the Paris Olympics closing ceremony Sunday as he started the engine on the handover to L.A. for the 2028 Summer Games.\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Corden\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 1.0493350927868385e-11, \"text\": \"James Corden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Corden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Corden\"}, {\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999816283130306, \"rank\": 1.837202471145543e-05, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo passed the Olympic flag to Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass (the first Black woman mayor to receive the official Olympic flag during a Closing Ceremony), and Simone Biles (the most decorated U.S. female gymnast of all time), Cruise leapt into the Stade de France before taking off on his motorcycle.\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2901369521432777e-24, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED:Paris Olympics Closing Ceremony In PicturesWatch on Deadline  TheMission: Impossiblestar, who interrupted filming of the latest installment of the action movie franchise to perform the stunt, then leapt from a plane to the Hollywood sign, passed the baton to Team USA Olympians including mountain biker Kate Courtney, track and field legend Michael Johnson\\u00a0and two-time Olympic medalist skateboarder Jagger Eaton, who took it to the beach - literally.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 879, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}, {\"begin\": 1138, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999992019184, \"rank\": 6.155643963596633e-10, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Courtney_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999981956923782, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Courtney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Courtney_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Courtney_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"score\": 0.6562406956374156, \"rank\": 0.2753288987434648, \"text\": \"Michael Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Johnson_(sprinter)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winston told Deadline that what viewers of the ceremony saw was almost identical to what he pitched Cruise, with one small difference.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I said to [Cruise], H.E.R.\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"does the national anthem, she starts rocking out her guitar.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We see a man on the roof in a balaclava.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He jumps off the roof, he grabs the flag, he drives through Paris, gets on the back of a plane, takes his balaclava off and we reveal it's you,\\\" Winston said.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9174704407175284e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[Cruise] said 'I absolutely love it, I am 100% in.'\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I remember how excited he was.\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said, 'There is only one thing.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no way that you are going to use a stuntman.\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It's me on that roof, I am jumping, I am doing it all.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no man in a balaclava'.\\\"\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 2019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was a year and a half ago.\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2052, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winston explained that with a stuntman it would only require one day of filming, rather than five or six.\", \"from\": 2053, \"to\": 2158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He was like, 'We either do it and we do it wholeheartedly and we do it fully, or we do not do it,' \\\" Winston added.\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's an incredible man, and just the single greatest collaborator you could ever work with.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's inspiring.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's hardworking, kind to everybody around him.\\\"\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Olympians took the flag across the city, there were performances by theRed Hot Chili Peppers, who performed \\\"Can not Stop\\\" from theirBy the Wayalbum, followed byBillie Eilishplaying \\\"Birds of a Feather\\\" on the top of a lifeguard tower.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ThenSnoop Dogg, arguably one of the breakout stars of the Olympics, performed \\\"Drop It Like It's Hot\\\" and teamed with Dr. Dre on a surprise performance of \\\"The Next Episode.\\\"\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a lot of amazing L.A. artists, there is a few other amazing hip hop stars like Kendrick Lamar being one, but those three were my first choice,\\\" Winston said.\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2884, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999816283130306, \"rank\": 1.837202471145543e-05, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 2946, \"end\": 2960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendrick_Lamar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4291190497469375e-62, \"text\": \"Kendrick Lamar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendrick_Lamar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendrick_Lamar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They were in my original deck before they even said yes a year and a half ago.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was so certain that when I was pitching the idea I already had Red Hot Chili Peppers on as the soundtrack to the Tom Cruise film,\\\" Winston added.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3170, \"end\": 3191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}, {\"begin\": 3220, \"end\": 3230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Winston, whose Fulwell73 produces series such as Hulu'sThe Kardashians, said he took his first meeting with LA28's Casey Wasserman in January 2022.\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3369, \"end\": 3384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casey Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The majority of it was shot live, although Winston admitted that some of it wasn't able to be shot live due to security concerns on the beach.\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Some people have said none of it was live.\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some said all of it's live.\", \"from\": 3590, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Actually, it's a bit in between, but for various different issues, because obviously you are exposed in the middle of the beach, and we had to keep it quiet what was happening for security reasons.\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If it had leaked where we were or what was happening, then we would have been shut down.\", \"from\": 3816, \"to\": 3904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am very aware that we can not afford to be shut down, because we are live to a billion people globally.\", \"from\": 3905, \"to\": 4010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a complicated project,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 4011, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Grammys exec producer admitted it was a bit tense.\", \"from\": 4053, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4057, \"end\": 4064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.9999998743478579, \"rank\": 1.1882406617605018e-07, \"text\": \"Grammys\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a very stressful one.\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was probably my highest stress levels I think I have ever had in my career.\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We had some tech issues connecting from Paris to L.A. You are combining so many elements that have to be played, and you are also kind of at the mercy of the Olympic broadcasting team, and the Paris team.\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4257, \"end\": 4262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9174704407175284e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4266, \"end\": 4270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999816283130306, \"rank\": 1.837202471145543e-05, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 4410, \"end\": 4415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9174704407175284e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a lot of technical stuff that was tricky and testing, and then you are also aware that the biggest movie star in the world was about to jump off a roof,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 4422, \"to\": 4595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winston and his team have plenty of experience in live television with projects such asElton John Live: Farewell from Dodgers StadiumandAdele: One Night Only.\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The live shows were directed by Hamish Hamilton, who has also directed a lot of live television.\", \"from\": 4757, \"to\": 4853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4789, \"end\": 4804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Hamilton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.898133255089034e-32, \"text\": \"Hamish Hamilton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Hamilton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Hamilton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Glenn Clements collaborated with Winston on the film, Dave Piendak and Raj Kapoor served as producers, Patrick Menton oversaw talent, and Misty Buckley and Gloria Lamb led set design for the beach concerts.\", \"from\": 4854, \"to\": 5060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4925, \"end\": 4935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raj_Kapoor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5298504667160468e-32, \"text\": \"Raj Kapoor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raj_Kapoor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raj_Kapoor\"}, {\"begin\": 4957, \"end\": 4964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"score\": 0.99999936768947, \"rank\": 6.322804960434113e-07, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 4965, \"end\": 4971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.172811575803589e-21, \"text\": \"Menton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Menton\"}, {\"begin\": 4992, \"end\": 4997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Millie_the_Model\", \"score\": 0.9999950680725054, \"rank\": 4.931952029410768e-06, \"text\": \"Misty\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q245068\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Millie_the_Model\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Millie_the_Model\"}, {\"begin\": 4998, \"end\": 5005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_F._Buckley_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.0518765729072116e-12, \"text\": \"Buckley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_F._Buckley_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_F._Buckley_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 5010, \"end\": 5016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gloria_Estefan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.573822137011063e-15, \"text\": \"Gloria\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gloria_Estefan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gloria_Estefan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a bit like when you have a baby and the baby comes and you are like, 'Oh my god, this is a nightmare stress, they are sick on you and need changing and then they turn 3 and they are really cute and you are like 'Let us do that again.'\", \"from\": 5062, \"to\": 5302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's a bit like live TV.\", \"from\": 5303, \"to\": 5329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When you are in it, you are asking why am I doing this?,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 5330, \"to\": 5396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Then I was looking around it yesterday and looking at the team, and I was like, 'We had had the greatest musicians in the world on that stage.\", \"from\": 5397, \"to\": 5540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We had Tom Cruise, the greatest movie star, and we also had the best of the best in our industry come and deliver it.'\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5548, \"end\": 5558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"  Get our Breaking News Alerts and Keep your inbox happy.\", \"from\": 5660, \"to\": 5718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5671, \"end\": 5684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breaking_news\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.4091146048366896e-21, \"text\": \"Breaking News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breaking_news\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breaking_news\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He should introduce couch jumping as an Olympic sport  What was in the bag on Tom Cruise's leg at he jumped from the roof?\", \"from\": 5720, \"to\": 5842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5798, \"end\": 5808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"